{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "Metallic Glass",
  "description": "Y2K-aesthetic feedback-displacement metallic surface generator.\n\nUpstream pipeline (unchanged): 3D simplex noise drives a feedback-blend loop (mix Difference + mix Lerp at 0.98) that builds an evolving liquid-mercury height field; two-axis Gaussian blur smooths the result. The smoothed height feeds (a) a levels-shaped height channel and (b) a mirror_axis → Sobel-magnitude chain that produces an edge / roughness modulation texture. Both channels then go through their own second-stage temporal blend (node.feedback + node.mix Lerp at 0.15) that matches the legacy bundle's packed-material smoothing pass. The smoothed height drives node.displace_mesh per-vertex, and node.heightmap_to_normal (WorldYUp) builds a world-space normal map at full canvas resolution.\n\nTerminal (refactored 2026-05-27 to the bundled PBR pipeline + mesh-UV sampling): node.render_3d_mesh draws the displaced grid in one forward pass — Cook-Torrance D_GGX × G_Smith × F_Schlick + IBL reflection — taking the world-space normal_map and the edge-derived roughness_map as per-pixel inputs sampled at each fragment's mesh UV. The envmap stays node.bake_equirect_envmap (the procedural HDR studio). All scattered cook_torrance_specular / equirect_envmap_sample / mix / reinhard_tone_map nodes are gone; the renderer handles shading internally and writes linear color straight to the final_output.\n\nWhy the rewrite: the legacy chain sampled the normal_map and world_pos at SCREEN UV in deferred-shading style, which silently broke as soon as render_3d_mesh became a true 3D forward renderer (texture pattern locked to the screen instead of the surface). The bundled PBR pipeline samples surface textures at MESH UV — the per-vertex parameterization interpolated through the rasterizer — so the lit pattern follows the geometry as the camera orbits, matching every production engine (Blender, Unreal, Unity, TouchDesigner). See docs/MESH_UV_AND_RENDERER_TEXTURE_PLAN.md.",
  "presetMetadata": {
    "id": "MetallicGlass",
    "displayName": "Metallic Glass",
    "category": "Generator",
    "oscPrefix": "metallicGlass",
    "legacyDiscriminant": 23,
    "available": true,
    "params": [
